'''Anza'''<ref name="Visual Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref> was a [[Fire|fiery]] [[Color|red]] [[star]]<ref name="Audio Description">{{TCW|Rising Malevolence|Rising ''Malevolence''}} {{AD|Netflix}}</ref> located in the [[Abregado system]]<ref name="Rising Malevolence" /> of [[the galaxy]]'s [[Core Worlds]]<ref name="Appendix" /> and [[the Interior]]<ref name="TheInterior" /> that was [[orbit]]ed by the [[planet]] [[Abregado-rae]],<ref name="Beginner Game" /> both of which were located in the grid square K-13 of the [[Standard Galactic Grid]].<ref name="Appendix" /> Its dim light provided enough energy to sustain life on Abregado-rae.<ref name="BMF 34" />

In [[22 BBY]],<ref name="Abregado-Date">{{TCWcanondates|102}}</ref> it was the site of the [[Battle of Abregado]] during the [[Clone Wars]], where the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist]] [[Subjugator-class heavy cruiser|''Subjugator''-class heavy cruiser]] ''[[Malevolence]]'' single-handedly annihilated an entire [[Galactic Republic|Republic]] [[fleet]]. The battle resulted in the formation of a [[Abregado debris field|debris field]], comprised of [[starship]] wreckage, in orbit of Anza.<ref name="Rising Malevolence" />

==Behind the scenes==
In the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]], the star of the Abregado [[Star system|system]] was created for "[[Rising Malevolence|Rising ''Malevolence'']],"<ref name="Rising Malevolence" /> the second episode of [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars''{{'}}]] [[The Clone Wars: Season One|first season]], which originally aired on [[October 3]], [[2008]].<ref name="RisingMalevolence-Epguide">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/guide/episode002.html|text=''The Clone Wars'' Episode Guide: Rising ''Malevolence''}}</ref> However, it first appeared in the opening newsreel of "[[Ambush]]," the first episode of the season<ref name="Ambush">{{TCW|Ambush}}</ref> that also aired on the same day.<ref name="Ambush air date">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/guide/episode001.html|text=''The Clone Wars'' Episode Guide: Ambush}}</ref>

The star [[Anza/Legends|Anza]] was originally introduced in ''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]'', a [[2003]] [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] sourcebook for the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="Coruscant and the Core Worlds">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref> The name was brought into canon by the [[2017]] reference book ''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''.<ref name="Visual Encyclopedia" />

